- Use nextjs latest version 15.3.1
- Use application router
- Use src configuration folder
- Use ES module
- Follow SOLID principles: Apply SOLID principles to write code that is easy to understand and maintain.
- Use TypeScript: Helps detect errors early and improve source code maintainability.
- Use Static Generation (SSG): Use getStaticProps to generate static pages, making pages load faster and improving SEO.
- Lazy loading and code splitting: Use next/dynamic to load components only when needed, reducing the size of the JavaScript ban of the size bundle.
- Use Link tags in navigation
- Optimize images: Use Next.js <Image> element to automatically optimize images, reducing page load time.


- Use Incremental Static Regeneration (ISR): Update page content without rebuilding the entire page, improving performance.